column5: Is anybody getting into OFN Community ? I'm getting error message #1000, shows me logged in and can't access anything. Tried Emailing [email protected] but returns failure notice.......Any ideas ?Thanks New Hips
No problem here. Maybe try another browser?
Tried Internet Explorer, at least can acess site, still wont work with Firefox, which I have always used.Thanks for the idea Solopaddler
I have tried to register with no luck too! Oh well, plenty of other things to do to fill in the time between trips!
I tried to register a couple of weeks ago and got no where. No response to my message either....I guess Walleye central it is.....

The problem as I was told, they're been inundated over the last few months with upwards of 200 bogus accounts a day.Most come from overseas but some use a proxy to appear as though they're in the States, so sometimes a genuine "new member" gets deleted, they're on a policy of "if it looks suspicious, delete."If they keep trying to register an account that also flags it as potential "spam bot," so it's hard to know who to let in these days. Not sure how kosher it is to post this on another site, but any WC members can pm me with whatever username they want register with on OFN and I'll pass it along.Cheers
Thanks, Mike...............that explains the block. I really don't need to post, but I like reading the members posts, some good information !
It took me over a week to be able to reply or post. It's another good source of info. Just want the bang for my buck
